# Overcast backend — risk-accepted HIGH/CRITICAL image findings, time-boxed.
# Reviewed 2026-07-12. Revisit by 2026-10-01 (Dependabot tracks upstream fixes).
#
# Each entry has NO published fix as of review: Trivy's DB cites a fixed version
# that is not yet on Maven Central. Accepted with the mitigation noted; remove
# the line the moment the fixed release lands (bumped by Dependabot).
#
# Everything else flagged (all 5 Tomcat CVEs, pgjdbc CVE-2025-49146, spring-boot
# CVE-2025-22235) IS remediated in pom.xml (Tomcat 10.1.55, pgjdbc 42.7.7,
# spring-boot 3.5.3) — not suppressed here.

# spring-boot: fix 3.5.14 unreleased (latest 3.5.3). Predictable actuator session
# id. Mitigated: actuator is not internet-exposed (ingress routes /api only),
# pods run non-root, namespace default-deny NetworkPolicy.
CVE-2026-40973

# spring-framework: fix 6.2.11 unreleased (latest 6.2.8). Annotation-detection
# issue with low reachability in this app's request paths.
CVE-2025-41249

# pgjdbc: fix 42.7.11 unreleased (latest 42.7.7 applied). Client-side DoS via a
# malicious SCRAM-SHA-256 response — the DB server is our own Azure SQL over a
# private endpoint, not an attacker-controlled host.
CVE-2026-42198
